<item>
            <title>[SPR-2422] Inconsistent terminology in MVC tutorial</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2422</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.springframework.org/docs/MVC-step-by-step/Spring-MVC-step-by-step-Part-1.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.springframework.org/docs/MVC-step-by-step/Spring-MVC-step-by-step-Part-1.html&lt;/a&gt; uses log4j.rootLogger in the example code, but the text above it still calls it log4j.rootCategory.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Even though they&apos;re basically equivalent, the former is preferred (&lt;a href=&quot;http://www.mail-archive.com/log4j-user@logging.apache.org/msg00614.html&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow&quot;&gt;http://www.mail-archive.com/log4j-user@logging.apache.org/msg00614.html&lt;/a&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Suggested fix: change &apos;rootCategory&apos; to &apos;rootLogger&apos;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
